    s = StringUtils.strip(s, STRIPPED_CHARS);  
    System.out.println(s);  // Gives : &quot;This str contains a non-breaking space and a	tab.&quot;




  [1]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/
  [2]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/javadocs/api-release/org/apache/commons/lang3/StringUtils.html#strip-java.lang.String-java.lang.String-

The logic behind the [`string.trim()`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#trim--) method is more or less the following (it does not use `charAt`, but the internal `byte[]` that stores the characters):

	public String trim(String s) {
		if (s == null) {
			return StringUtils.EMPTY;
		}
		int originalLength = s.length();
		int start = 0;
		int end = originalLength;
		while (start &lt; end &amp;&amp; isTrimmable(s.charAt(start))) {
			start++;
		}
		while (start &lt; end &amp;&amp; isTrimmable(s.charAt(end-1))) {
			end--;
		}
		return ((start &gt; 0) || (end &lt; originalLength)) ? s.substring(start, end) : s;
	}

where `isTrimmable` means less or equal `&#39;\u0020&#39;`. You can implement an util method with custom logic to detect trimmable characters without using a regex:

    public static String fullTrim(String s) {
        if (s == null) {
            return StringUtils.EMPTY;
        }
        int originalLength = s.length();
        int start = 0;
        int end = originalLength;
        while (start &lt; end &amp;&amp; isTrimmable(s.charAt(start))) {
            start++;
        }
        while (start &lt; end &amp;&amp; isTrimmable(s.charAt(end-1))) {
            end--;
        }
        return ((start &gt; 0) || (end &lt; originalLength)) ? s.substring(start, end) : s;
    }

    public static boolean isTrimmable(char c) {
        return Character.isWhitespace(c) || c == &#39;\u00A0&#39; || c == &#39;\u2007&#39; || c == &#39;\u202F&#39;;
    }

This is a solution that doesn&#39;t use a regex or the (equivalent) [StringUtils.strip(string, charactersToStrip)](https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/apidocs/org/apache/commons/lang3/StringUtils.html#strip-java.lang.String-java.lang.String-), as I prefer to maintain a `isTrimmable` method than a `charactersToStrip`/regex string.

